; Regression test for issue #958: Fixated prices vanish when commodity equivalencies exist (BZ#958)
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/958
;
; When a commodity equivalency (C directive) exists for a commodity that also
; has a fixated lot price ({=...}), the fixated price annotation is lost and
; the market price is used instead. The correct behavior is for the fixated
; price to take precedence over market prices.

C 1 AAPL = 1 share

P 2024/06/01 AAPL $200.00

2024/01/01 Buy AAPL
    Assets:Brokerage    10 AAPL {=$100.00}
    Assets:Cash        $-1000.00

test bal -V Assets:Brokerage
            $2000.00  Assets:Brokerage
end test
